STATE of Missouri, Respondent,
v.
Travis Dewayne COATS, Appellant. WD 81024 Missouri Court of Appeals, Western District. ORDER FILED: July 3, 2018 Christian Lehmberg, Columbia, MO, Counsel for Appellant. Risa Perkins, Fulton, MO, Counsel for Respondent. Before Division One: Lisa White Hardwick, P.J., Thomas H. Newton, and Edward R. Ardini, JJ.

ORDER

Per Curiam:

Mr. Travis Dewayne Coats appeals his conviction by a Callaway County jury of two counts of third-degree domestic assault. § 565.074, RSMo. (2000 and 2012 Supp.). The trial court sentenced him to ninety days of incarceration in jail on each count to be served concurrently but suspended execution of sentence, placing Mr. Coats on two years of supervised probation. For reasons stated in the memorandum provided to the parties, we affirm. Rule 30.25(b).
